Under

Rashid , Microsoft is investing heavily --- about $6 billion annually, according to estimates in trade publications --- into research into computer vision, e-Commerce applications and Web services, including search engine technology. Work done at Microsoft Research has led directly to creation of:

Microsoft Virtual Earth and TerraServer;

Data mining and machine-learning tools on the company's SQL Servers;

Compression and encoding algorithms of Windows Media Player; and

